# 🛡️ ALL SAFE 2.0 — Flow Diagrams

> Complete system architecture and data flow documentation for the ALL SAFE Cybersecurity Platform.

---

## 1. System Architecture Overview

![System Architecture — 3-tier: Frontend (React+Vite) → Backend (FastAPI) → External APIs (VirusTotal, Gemini, etc.)](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\system_architecture_1772912711100.png)

> **Frontend** (React + Vite) communicates with the **Backend** (FastAPI + Python) via REST and WebSocket. The Backend queries **External APIs** like VirusTotal, AbuseIPDB, HoneyDB, Google Gemini AI, and Groq LLaMA.

---

## 2. AI Chatbot Flow

![AI Chatbot Flow — Message lifecycle from user input through intent parsing, scan execution, AI response generation, to bubble rendering](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\chatbot_flow_1772912728143.png)

> The chatbot uses an **Intent Router** (AI-powered) to parse user messages and automatically trigger scans (URL, IP, Hash, Domain, Email, Job Scam). Results are fed as context to the AI for a comprehensive reply. **Gemini is primary, Groq LLaMA is the fallback.**

---

## 3. Threat Scanner Pipeline

![Threat Scanner Flow — Auto-detect input type, query external APIs, calculate risk level (CLEAN/LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH), generate AI summary](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\scanner_flow_1772912744854.png)

> The scanner **auto-detects** input type (URL, IP, Hash, Domain, Email, Phone, File) and routes to the appropriate API. Risk is calculated from detection counts: 🟢 CLEAN → 🟡 LOW → 🟠 MEDIUM → 🔴 HIGH.

---

## 4. Live Threat Map Flow

![Live Threat Map — Real-time data from ThreatFox, AbuseIPDB, HoneyDB feeds, WebSocket broadcast to globe visualization](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\live_map_flow_1772912786612.png)

> Every 60 seconds, the backend fetches threats from **ThreatFox, AbuseIPDB, and HoneyDB**, geolocates IPs, and broadcasts updates via **WebSocket** to the Live Map globe visualization.

---

## 5. Job Scam Detection Flow

![Job Scam Detection — Rule-based pattern matching (8 weighted rules) + Gemini AI analysis → risk classification (SCAM/SUSPICIOUS/LEGITIMATE)](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\job_scam_flow_1772912800264.png)

> Combines **8 rule-based pattern checks** (upfront fees, unrealistic salary, urgency tactics, etc.) with **Gemini AI deep analysis** for accurate scam classification.

---

## 6. AI Engine Failover Chain

![AI Failover — Dual Gemini API keys with Groq LLaMA fallback chain for 99.9% uptime](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\ai_failover_flow_1772912818512.png)

> Two Gemini API keys provide redundancy. If both fail, the system falls back to **Groq LLaMA 3.3 70B**. The reverse applies when Groq is explicitly selected.

---

## 7. Database & Logging Architecture

![Database Architecture — SQLite with scans and shared_reports tables, log_scan() pipeline, report sharing tokens](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\database_flow_1772912860564.png)

> All scans are logged to **SQLite** with type, target, JSON result, risk level, and timestamp. Reports can be shared via unique tokens.

---

## 8. Frontend Component Tree

![React Component Tree — App.jsx root with 7 global components, 9 page components, and sub-components for Chatbot and Scanner](C:\Users\mahen\.gemini\antigravity\brain\1f67c5cb-f2fb-408b-9360-5493c5ef10e6\component_tree_1772912877295.png)

> **17 React components** organized in a clean hierarchy. [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/mahen/OneDrive/Apps/NEXATHAN/frontend/src/App.jsx) manages routing between 9 pages with animated transitions.

